Two men, Pelumi Joseph, 20, and Lekan Arawole, 25, were on Tuesday remanded in Agodi Prison by an Iyaganku Chief Magistrates’ Court in Ibadan on Tuesday for alleged armed robbery. Chief Magistrate Kehinde Omotosho ordered that Joseph and Arawole be remanded in Agodi prison pending the receipt of legal advice from the office of the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP). The plea of the defendants was not also taken by the court. Omotosho adjourned the case till Jan.11, 2019 for mention. The News Agency of Nigeria reports that Joseph and Arawole of unknown addresses are facing a two-count charge of conspiracy and armed robbery. The Prosecutor, Inspector Sunday Fatola, had told the court that the defendants conspired to commit the offences. Fatola said Joseph and Arawole on Oct.22 at about 6 a.m. at Akingbile area, Moniya, Ibadan, allegedly attacked one Abubakar Abdullahi, a commercial motorcyclist. He said that the defendants were armed with a jackknife and other dangerous weapons when they attacked the complainant. “The defendants allegedly dispossessed Abdullahi of his boxer Bajaj motorcycle with registration number  AGG 963 QS valued at N120, 000,’’ Fatola said. He said the offences contravened Section 1 (2) and 6 (B) of the Armed Robbery and Firearms (Special Provision) Act Cap RII, Vol. 14, Laws of the Federal Republic of Nigeria 2004.